# Angular Frontend Edit Rules

1. Execute precise delta insertions on TS components, structural blocks, or HTML templates. Do not reprint adjacent `@Component` decorators, imports, or class boilerplate.
2. `effect()` calls MUST live in class field initializers or the `constructor()` — never inside `ngOnInit`, `ngOnChanges`, or other lifecycle/custom methods (NG0203).
3. State uses Angular Signals (`signal`, `computed`, `effect`). Avoid RxJS Subjects for new component state unless interop is required.
4. Inject dependencies with field-level `inject(...)` rather than constructor parameter DI for new code.
5. Styling: Vanilla CSS with `var(--color-*)` tokens from `src/index.css`. Do NOT introduce Tailwind, utility frameworks, or new global stylesheets.
6. Mask sensitive user fields in templates (e.g. `user.email_masked || user.email`).
7. Respect Angular bundle budgets — keep deps lean; verify with `npm run build` after non-trivial changes.
8. Use omission markers `// ... existing code ...` (TS/JS) and `<!-- ... existing code -->` (HTML) when truncating context in chat snippets.
